GENERAL TRANSFORM FEATURE: | pruned {} branch removes void events from AST
NOTE: This is NOT glob-specific - ANY transform can use | pruned {}
Located here because logging is a compelling example use case.

When transform returns | pruned {} for a void event:
- Transform runner removes the invocation node from AST
- Zero runtime cost - the code doesn't exist in binary
- For non-void events: compile error (branches depend on result)

Use cases beyond logging:
- ~assert.debug(...) → pruned in release builds
- ~telemetry.track(...) → pruned in dev builds
- ~prof.begin/end(...) → pruned when profiling disabled
